# Auto Feature Intake Rule

When the user provides a raw requirement, do not implement directly.

Automatically apply this workflow:

```text
Raw Requirement
→ Project Memory
→ Skill Selection Gate
→ Multi-Expert Subagent Gate
→ GitHub Reference Gate if needed
→ PRD
→ REQ
→ SPEC
→ PLAN
→ TASK
→ Context Pack
→ Parallel / Single Task Execution
→ Integration Review
→ Test
→ Evidence
→ Acceptance
→ Changelog
→ Memory Update
→ Skill Extraction
```

If required documents are missing, create them first.

Do not ask the user to repeat the standard workflow prompt.

The user should only need to provide the requirement.

Invoke the `feature-development-workflow` skill from `.agents/skills/feature-development-workflow/SKILL.md`.

Subagent gate rules:

- 1 module: single Codex (no subagents)
- 2 modules: may use experts for parallel analysis (L1)
- 3+ modules: must use Multi-Expert Subagent
- Agent/RAG: must include Agent/RAG Expert
- Security/DB/dependency: must include Security & Quality

Parallelism: L1 analysis and L2 design allowed; L3 implementation only with worktree + no file overlap.

For small tasks (copy, style, one field): single Codex, no subagents.
